  <front>
   <head>SONNET [58] LVIII. The Glow Worm.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">WHEN, on some balmy breathing night of Spring,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The happy child, to whom the world is new,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Pursues the evening moth, of mealy wing,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Or from the heathbell beats the sparkling dew;</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">He sees before his inexperienc'd eyes,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The brilliant Glow Worm, like a meteor, shine</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">On the turf bank; — amaz'd and pleas'd he cries</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">'Star of the dewy grass! — I make thee mine!'.</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Then, ere he sleep, collects 'the moisten'd' flow'r,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And bids soft leaves his glittering prize enfold,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And dreams that fairy lamps illume his bow'r:</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Yet with the morning, shudders to behold</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">His lucid treasure, rayless as the dust;</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+||-+|-+|-+" line_length="12">So turn the world's bright joys, to cold and blank disgust.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
